725945f-b.title: Queens: 163rd Street - Jamaica Avenue
725945f-b.text:
163rd Street, (formerly No. 26 Hardenbrook Avenue) east side,
north of Jamaica Avenue, showing in a set of two views the Reverend
Wm. L. Johnson house, who was the rector of the First Rresbyterian
CNurck of Jamaica between 1830 and 1870 when he died. IIt subsequently
became the property of Wm. Hardenbrook who was born in 1810 at
Freeport. He settled in Jamaica where he purchased several acres
in what is now the business section and opened the thoroughfare
upon which this structure stands in 1890. This building originally
stood on Jamaica Avenue when same was known as Fulton Street.
May i923.
